Common Interview Questions
Q1. What is the difference between cp and mv?
cp creates a copy and keeps the original.
mv moves or renames the original.
Q2. What is the difference between an absolute path and a relative path?
Absolute path: Starts from / (root directory).
Relative path: Starts from your current working directory.
Q3. Why is rm -rf considered dangerous?

Because it recursively and forcefully deletes files and directories without asking for confirmation.

Q4. What does grep do?

grep searches for a specified pattern or text inside one or more files.

Q5. Why should AI engineers learn Linux?

Because AI training, deployment, cloud servers, Docker containers, and most production ML infrastructure run on Linux systems.